fields.name: Soft Wash
fields.label: Soft Wash
fields.description: Soft washing is a gentle cleaning method that uses a low-pressure spray and specialized cleaning solution to remove dirt, grime, and other debris from surfaces such as buildings, roofs, and sidewalks. It is often used on delicate surfaces and to remove difficult stains, and is effective at restoring the appearance of many surfaces.
fields.details: Soft washing is a cleaning method that uses a low-pressure spray and a specialized cleaning solution to gently remove dirt, grime, and other debris from surfaces such as buildings, roofs, and sidewalks. This method is effective at cleaning delicate surfaces and removing difficult stains, and it can be used on a variety of surfaces. To soft wash, the surface is prepared, the cleaning solution is applied with a low-pressure spray and left to penetrate, then rinsed off with low-pressure water. Soft washing is a gentle yet effective method that can restore the appearance of many surfaces and is often used for commercial and residential cleaning projects. It is particularly effective at removing algae, mold, and other types of growth that accumulate over time.

fields.name: Pressure Wash
fields.label: Power Wash
fields.description: Pressure washing, also known as power washing, involves using a high-pressure stream of water to blast away dirt, grime, and other types of debris from surfaces such as buildings, sidewalks, decks, and more. This method is highly effective at removing tough stains and built-up dirt that cannot be easily removed through traditional cleaning methods.
fields.details: Pressure washing, also known as power washing, is a cleaning method that uses a high-pressure stream of water to remove dirt, grime, and other types of debris from surfaces such as buildings, sidewalks, decks, and more. A pressure washer machine is set up and connected to a water source, and the pressure and flow rate of the water stream can be adjusted. A cleaning solution may also be used. The pressure washer wand is aimed at the surface being cleaned and the water stream is applied in a sweeping motion. After the surface has been cleaned, it is allowed to air dry or is wiped down with a clean, dry cloth. Pressure washing is often used for commercial and industrial cleaning, as well as for residential projects.

fields.name: Roof Wash
fields.label: Soft Wash
fields.description: Soft washing a roof is a gentle method of cleaning delicate roof materials such as asphalt shingles, tile, or wood. This process cleans the roof without damaging it and helps extend its lifespan. It's important to check that the cleaning solution used is safe for the roof material, and the pressure is set correctly to avoid any damage.
fields.details: Soft washing a roof is a gentle and effective method to remove dirt, grime, and other debris from delicate roof materials such as asphalt shingles, tile or wood. The process begins by preparing the area around the roof, then a specialized cleaning solution is applied to the roof surface using a low-pressure spray. The solution is left on the roof for a specified period of time, typically 15-20 minutes, to penetrate and break down the dirt, stains and other contaminants. After that, the solution is rinsed off with low-pressure water, removing the dirt and stains without damaging the roof. The end result is a cleaner, fresher-looking roof that will last longer as well as add value to the property. It's important to check that the cleaning solution used is safe for the roof material, and the pressure is set correctly to avoid any damage.

fields.name: Concrete Scrub
fields.label: Mosmatic High Pressure Washer
fields.description: Pressure washing a flat concrete surface with a Mosmatic High Pressure Commercial FL-CR 750 30in 80.772 can remove dirt, grime, stains, and other debris, as well as mold and mildew, to improve the surface's appearance and longevity.
fields.details: Pressure washing a flat concrete surface with a Mosmatic High Pressure Commercial FL-CR 750 30in 80.772 can provide several benefits. One of the main benefits is the ability to effectively remove dirt, grime, and other debris that can accumulate on the surface over time. This can help to restore the appearance of the concrete and make it look like new again. In addition, pressure washing can help to remove stains and other discolorations that can occur on concrete surfaces due to exposure to the elements or other factors. Pressure washing can also help to remove mold, mildew, and other types of growth that can occur on concrete, which can be unsightly and potentially harmful to the surface. Overall, pressure washing a flat concrete surface with a high pressure washer can help to maintain the appearance and longevity of the surface.
